From: everyx <lunt.luo@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 10:24:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix network initialization during system boot

During Linux system boot, the network stack may not be fully initialized
when sing-box starts. The original code would trigger NetworkPause() for
missing default interface, preventing automatic recovery after network
initialization completes.

Skip pause handling when not started to allow proper initialization.

diff --git a/route/network.go b/route/network.go
index 37761fd2..8be2929a 100644
--- a/route/network.go
+++ b/route/network.go
@@ -485,7 +485,7 @@ func (r *NetworkManager) ResetNetwork() {
 }
 
 func (r *NetworkManager) notifyInterfaceUpdate(defaultInterface *control.Interface, flags int) {
-	if defaultInterface == nil {
+	if defaultInterface == nil && r.started {
 		r.pauseManager.NetworkPause()
 		r.logger.Error("missing default interface")
 		return
-- 
